label("$A$", pA, SE);
label("$B$", pB, NE);
label("$C$", pC, W);
draw(circle(pO, 1));
[/asy] If $AC = BC$ and $\angle OAC = 18^\circ,$ then how many degrees are in $\angle AOB$?

answer:
First, let us draw $CO$: [asy]
pair pA, pB, pC, pO;
pO = (0, 0);
pA = pO + dir(-40);
pB = pO + dir(32);
pC = pO + dir(176);
draw(pA--pO--pB--pC--pA);
draw(pO--pC);
